    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="transcript" id="P91-123">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>It sifts from leaden sieves,</l>
                    <l>It powders all the wood,</l>
                    <l>It fills with alabaster wool</l>
                    <l>The wrinkles of the road.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>It makes an even face</l>
                    <l>Of mountain and of plain, </l>
                    <l>Unbroken forehead from the east</l>
                    <l>Unto the east again.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>It reaches to the fence,</l>
                    <l>It wraps it, rail by rail,</l>
                    <l>Till it is lost in fleeces;</l>
                    <l>It flings a crystal veil</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>On stump and stack and stem, </l>
                    <l>The summer's empty room,</l>
                    <l>Acres of seams where harvests were,</l>
                    <l>Recordless, but for them.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>It ruffles wrists of posts,</l>
                    <l>As ankles of a queen, </l>
                    <l>Then stills its artisans like ghosts,</l>
                    <l>Denying they have been.</l>
                </lg>

            </div>     
